 <p>At boot a file is created at /var/logs/untetherhomedepotLoopProtection.txt
 <p>which contains the number of times the exploit failed.
 <p>If the number exceeds "10" then the untether boots without executing the kernelexploit.
 <p>On every successfull boot the file is deleted.
 <p>If you want to deactivate untether then run:
 <p>"echo '10' > /var/logs/untetherhomedepotLoopProtection.txt"
 <br>
 There is an offsets.json file in /untether
 <p>You should really not touch any of the files shipped with this package!
 <p>However if you don't care about your device bootlooping, you
 <p>might want to try your luck and add offsets to the file.
 <p>But please keep in mind:
 <p>MODIFYING THIS FILE CAN CAUSE BOOTLOOPS!
 <br>
 FINAL WARNING:
 <p>INSTALL AT YOUR OWN RISK!!!!!
